MBOMBELA – i’langa Mall management has responded in a report to a voice note claiming a woman was nearly kidnapped at its establishment. The report states that the allegation was completely unfounded.  It reads, “Spreading false news like this can cause you to get into serious trouble. No proof was given and no names are ever mentioned. If you know exactly who was nearly kidnapped, please report it to the management at the mall as this is a very serious issue. “The danger is real, yes, but there have not been any such incidents in Mbombela. Please check facts before ‘sharing’ news.  This can open you to a case of defamation. i’langa Mall is taking this matter very seriously.”